SIMPLE: recriminate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recriminate
<hw>Re*crim"i*nate</hw> <pr>(r?*kr?m"?*n?t)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> + <ets>criminate</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧criminer</ets>, LL. <ets>recriminare</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
return one charge or accusation with another; to charge back fault or
crime upon an accuser.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is not my business to <qex>recriminate</qex>, hoping
sufficiently to clear myself in this matter.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recriminate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recriminate
<hw>Re*crim"i*nate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To accuse in
return.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recrimination</ent>⟦br⟧
